frameDefinitions: There is a gradable amount of light in a particular Location.
These words relate to the relative ordering of two events or times.

An Agent or Potential_hindrance keeps a Protagonist from having a State_of_affairs that they need or desire, or, despite the possibility of preventing the possession, they allow the Protagonist to have the State_of_affairs.
A Sound emitted by a  Sound_source, which construed as a single point, moves along a Path.
A volitionally acting Interceptor takes control, without being authorized to do so by the sender, of a Theme that is underway from a sender to a recipient.
In this frame a Preventing_cause interferes with the ability of a Protagonist to complete an intended Action.
frameExamples: The small print was bearly readable by the light of the very <t>dim</t> torch.
<t>After</t> she arrived , she laid out her papers on the desk.
His parents <t>deprived</t> him of food for days on end.
Her shouts <t>echoed</t> around the cylinder formed by the walls.
Police <t>intercepted</t> the call and raided the address.
listRoleDefinitions: The place whose amout of light is being described.  The <fen>Location</fen> can also be a location in time, as seen in the second example below:
The entity from which the light eminates.

The <fen>Focal_occasion</fen> is the event which is  being located in time with respect to some other event: The <fen>Focal_occasion</fen> is profiled, in contrast to the <fen>Landmark_occasion</fen>, which is backgrounded.
The <fen>Landmark_occasion</fen> is the event  with respect to which the <fen>Focal_occasion</fen> is located.
The <fen>Focal_participant</fen> is the participant in the <fen>Focal_occasion</fen> which is profiled as being in a relation of relative time to the <fen>Landmark_occasion</fen>.
The <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> is the force which keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from happening, or does not prevent it.
The  is the situation, state-of-affairs, or state of having a possession that the <fen>Protagonist</fen> is kept from having.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the  person who keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from happening.
The <fen>Protagonist</fen> is the person who is kept from having the <fen>State_of_affairs</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
A percept produced  in hearing organs by  vibrations which travel through the air or another medium.
The location of the Sound_source from which the <fen>Sound</fen> travels
The Path of the Sound's movement is any description of its trajectory of motion which is neither a Location_of_sound_source or a Goal.
The point-like entity which produces the <fen>Sound</fen>.
A description of the location where the <fen>Sound</fen> ends up.
The time when  the <fen>Sound</fen> movement occurs.
A setting in which <fen>Sound</fen> movement happens.
The volitional agent who without authorization of sender or recipient takes control of a <fen>Theme</fen> that is en route to a destination.
The entity, physical or abstract, construed as traveling from a sender to a goal location, which is taken hold of by the <fen>Interceptor</fen> without permission.
The time period during which the <fen>Interceptor</fen> takes control of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location at which the <fen>Interceptor</fen> takes control of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Preventing_cause</fen> is the agent or force who keeps the <fen>Protagonist</fen> from completing her or his planned <fen>Action</fen>.
The <fen>Protagonist</fen> is the individual or group of individuals who have a planned <fen>Action</fen> which is prevented by the <fen>Preventing_cause</fen>
The <fen>Action</fen> is the action or event certain individuals desire to bring about which is prevented by the <fen>Preventing_cause</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the thwarting occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the thwarting occurs.

A dim <fex>lamp</fex> swung over the entrance to the castle.
<fex>Hours of eating and drinking</fex> followed the wedding ceremony.
Hours of eating and drinking followed <fex>the wedding ceremony</fex>.
<fex>Israeli law</fex> effectively deprived the owners of their homes and lands.
Their parents denied them <fex>a brand new car</fex> upon their sweet 16.
<fex>The uncaring King Frank</fex> often starves his citizens of tax relief.
The Prince 's laugh echoed <fex>from the corridor</fex>.
A loud bang echoed <fex>through the valley</fex>.
There was muzak echoing <fex>from cheap speakers</fex>.
<fex>In the mornings</fex> the harsh , squawking voices of the gulls echo between the channel walls
I heard their footsteps echo <fex>in the hollow cavern</fex>.
Two days later, <fex>an aerial patrol</fex> intercepted an enemy trying the same thing.
They could either sail west down the Channel or north-east to intercept <fex>an enemy making for the Thames estuary</fex>.
The five had been intercepted <fex>after a DFLP attack on March 5</fex>.
She had been intercepted <fex>outside Guy 's room</fex> and would be severely punished.
